<br>
She noticed Scooby's growling but she had already been aware of this and had watched Scooby get off.. this was too bad, she couldn't go back and get him. She reached for her map, pulled it out and was stunned. They seem to move quite quickly... well... they were reptillian people. Delilah called to Alysia, &quot;Gaurd yourself! They are about!&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked at the map.. they were ahead in the woods and were going to be behind us. We were riding into a trap, a circle... This wasn't good... &quot;Alysia! We're slowly being surrounded! Tell the others to pull out their weapons!&quot;<br>
<br>
This would be where the war takes place... in and around this clearing and the woods. The amazons knew these woods though, we'll have a better advantage to the Saurians. Delilah clicked her tongue and her eyes went purple... she had begun muttering.<br>
<br>
This muttering caused a second horse-like tiger to suddenly spring up from the ground and run beside her own. Delilah waved a hand and this unseated Evelyn. Evelyn of them flew onto the second horse-sized tiger. She double-clicked her tongue then gave a low whistle to the second tiger. It moved off to the woods, to the very edge and crouched their, a new seating charm also placed on Evelyn to keep them on the sitting tiger so they could not enter the war, but only watch.  Delilah's eyes glittered a gold color before turning red. Suddenly, to every and any eye that would look Evelyn's way, the section she sat in looked like nothing but old logs that woul be of no help to anyone or anything. Anywho who would look there would not spot Evelyn or her second tiger. So there they would sit, to watch the war.. kind of like front row seats you could say.<br>
<br>
Delilah clicked her tongue to her own tiger and it slowed down a considerable amount. Delilah's eyes, now red, scanned the forests and she could see the many movements. She couldn't tell if this would be the first battle of the war... or the big fight itself.. all she could tell was that... well... they have been closed in and would have to fight all the Saurians to break the trap.<br>
<br>
She drew her sword with her left. She was strong with both arms and they both functioned equally. She narrowed her eyes, the fight... would soon begin. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udelilahtragedy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Delilah Tragedy</A> at: 8/23/01 2:31:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 200<br> <font color=#993300>(8/23/01 2:50:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Movement in the Woods</span><hr size=1> Alysia turned to look at Delilah as she scanned the woods as well seeing some movements.<br>
